An Iran national armed with two knives, a machete, and a pickax has been detained by police officers not far from US President Donald Trump’s Mar-a-Lago residence in Florida, media reported on Saturday. The incident occurred around 1430 hrs (GMT). The police got reports about a ‘suspicious person’ in Bradley Park, four miles from Trump’s private resort. According to the report of Washington Examiner which cited the police authorities a man named as Masoud Yareilzoleh, an Iran national staying legally in the US was arrested on charges related to carrying concealed weapons. Officer Michael Ogrodnick told the outlet the man had a car parked at Palm Beach International Airport and that federal authorities were collaborating in an investigation.